snippet.textDisplay:
I thought the players went onto the pitch cold, I can't understand why their was no pre-training before the game, in their stadium? LFC released a pre-match training on Monday, but it was at Liverpool before they flew out.

You need a warm up,in the stadium your playing, and then we got caught out cold, in the 1st 5 minutes.

Saying that, 3 strikers up front, away from home, and the 1st leg, you don't need to do keep doing it. Klopp should have had Lovren and Matip and Dyke playing. This was a final, on their ground. Change it, 60-70 minutes, and stretch them,

Klopp keeps making this error, and just runs with casual approach, lets see, etc. Its not only about who runs and wants it the most, its about formations, what's at stake, who your playing, Klopp is naive,

Athletico are used to big games, they beat Barcelona in January in Spanish Super Cup, and took Real Madrid to penalties.

snippet.textDisplay: You're just clueless. You received a football lesson. Our tactics, our game plan, the execution, the chances... Liverpool didn't manage to get a simple shot on target, and you just got one more shot than us. Statistics and match are two separate things. The statistics show the actions that were done in the match. But, the match shows both teams' performance. Our performance was slightly better than yours, because despite having 70% possession, our chances were more clear than yours. The Morata slip, Costa's mistake, Morata's header, Lodi's cross deflected by Robbo... And Liverpool? What clear chances did Liverpool have? Henderson's one, and even Salah's missed header. ONLY TWO CLEAR CHANCES. The rest of the game was your midfield passing the ball between them.
